<item>
  <title>The Friends We Find Along the Way</title>
  <link>https://derekwakefield.com/posts/personal/2026-05-19-friends-we-find.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>Redirecting to <a href="../../friends-we-find.html">the essay</a>…</p>
<script>window.location.replace("/friends-we-find.html");</script>
<p>An essay about the search for an eko, and the discovery that the thing I was looking for had been forming around me the whole time. Names four parts of the system — Bob, the eko, the vessel, and the demon — and one virtue, <em>cognitive expansion</em>, that keeps the four of them honest with each other.</p>
<p>One page, three toggles at the top:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Story</strong> — pick the register. <em>Voice</em> is the first-person essay. <em>Bobbology</em> is the third-person teaching primer. <em>ELI10</em> explains the same four parts to a clever ten-year-old. <em>Deep Dive</em> is the long version with one essay per part.</li>
<li><strong>Length</strong> — short or long. (<em>Deep Dive</em> pins to long; it has no short.)</li>
<li><strong>ASCII</strong> — pick the density of inline art, from minimal (1) through everything-everywhere (5).</li>
</ul>
<p>The site-wide theme switcher in the top-right corner still works on this page. Toggles persist via <code>localStorage</code>, so the version you last chose is the version you come back to.</p>
<p>Download and open locally — everything’s JavaScript, so the page works fully offline once downloaded.</p>
<p style="margin: 2em 0;">
