<p>A short essay about a month spent with an AI as a thinking partner — what worked, what didn’t, what almost broke, and what came back through people.</p>
<p>Two versions live in one page. A small toggle at the top switches between them. The short version is a single-arc Modern Love–shaped cut (around thirteen paragraphs). The long version is the full ten-section essay, with section markers. Both share the same starfield and the same drifting ASCII creatures behind the text.</p>
<p>Download and open locally — the toggle is JavaScript, so the file works fully offline once downloaded.</p>
